# Outbound email standards

Canonical detail lives in `docs/AGENTS.md` (**Outgoing email**). Keep this rule aligned; do not let the two drift.

Every outbound email from domesti-bot MUST:

1. **Provenance** — End the body (plain + HTML) with:
   ```text
   Sent by: domesti-bot · <subsystem> (<trigger>)
   ```
   Prefer `app.outbound_email.provenance_footer` (and related helpers in `app.outbound_email`, including `build_outbound_message` / `deliver_outbound_email` for MIME + send). The SMTP `From:` address is not sufficient.

2. **Instance URL** — When a public base URL is known (`DOMESTI_PUBLIC_BASE_URL` or My Tracks pair status, or the live UI origin for Settings tests), include the instance top-level URL in the body. Prefer an Automations deep link (`#/automations/…`) in addition when the mail concerns something editable there. Do not invent broken hash routes.

3. **Human-friendly copy** — Plain language; no jargon-only bodies (e.g. “hysteresis window” without concrete wait / distance / users / home).

4. **Concrete facts** — Include the values an operator needs to verify the decision (users, home label + lat/lon, distance **thresholds**, dwell durations). When the decision depends on how far a user is from **home** or a **geofence**, also report the **observed** distance(s) (and which geofence / home point) when those readings are available.

5. **Test vs real** — Settings / Automations / Mail **test** sends must mark the subject with `[test]`, state that the message is a test, and state when live state was not changed.

6. **Closed sets** — When code branches on send source, use a `StrEnum` (`python-closed-set-enums.mdc`).

7. **Example addresses** — Tracked fixtures use `@example.com` only (`example-email-addresses.mdc`).
